content:
Since a few days my Pixel 3A won't charge properly. Details:

It will only charge once every so many tries;
It will only charge through USB-C to USB-A via my laptop (not through any other cables, including the one provided when I bought the phone and not through any other outlets);
It will only charge when turned off;
It charges extremely slow (more than 1 hour per 1%);
It will randomly turn on when charging;
It will randomly shut down while still having some power;
The power usage is very high (loses about 20% per hour without using it);

Things I have tried:
Cleaning the USB-C connector on my phone and all cables;
Different cables, different outlets;
Charging while on/off;
Soft reset;
Putting it back to factory settings;
Connect to Update and Software Repair by Google in repair mode, however my phone cannot connect as that is where the problem seems to be.

I live in The Netherlands and ordered it from France on the 22nd of June this year. I cannot find any repair options on the website. When I click any link it will automatically send me back to the Google store homepage. The chat option on the website also doesn't work. I have found similar problems on this forum but without any real solutions. The problems seem to disappear automatically or the question is just left open. 

I think it could be software related and might have something to do with an update, but I am unsure. I am at a loss for what to do and could really use some help. The phone is only a few months old and I really don't have any money for a new one. If warranty is an option and someone has info on that, that would be greatly appreciated as well, I cannot find any info on where to send my phone for warranty or repair.

Thank you so much in advance!
